   "body" : "### Is there an existing issue for this?\n\n- [X] I have searched the existing issues\n\n### Current behaviour\n\nI am creating a tx using:\r\n\r\n$ bitcoin-cli createrawtransaction '''                                         \r\n[{\"txid\":\"7b6412a0eed56338731e83c606f13ebb7a3756b3e4e1dbbe43a7db8d09106e56\",\"vout\": 1}]\r\n''' '''{\"mtVHHCqCECGwiMbMoZe8ayhJHuTdDbYWdJ\": 0.00004}'''\r\n0200000001566e10098ddba743bedbe1e4b356377abb3ef106c6831e733863d5eea012647b0100000000`fdffffff`01a00f0000000000001976a9148e48a6c5108efac226d33018b5347bb24adec37a88ac00000000\r\n\r\nThe nSequence (highlighted above) has RBF enabled. This is the default behaviour. I have stopped the node, added `walletrbf=0` to `bitcoin.conf` in order to disable RBF, restarted, but it does not work (result of `createrawtransaction` is identical). \n\n### Expected behaviour\n\nI expected the nSequence field to be `ffffffff`.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n$ bitcoin-cli createrawtransaction '''\r\n[{\"txid\":\"7b6412a0eed56338731e83c606f13ebb7a3756b3e4e1dbbe43a7db8d09106e56\",\"vout\": 1}]\r\n''' '''{\"mtVHHCqCECGwiMbMoZe8ayhJHuTdDbYWdJ\": 0.00004}'''\n\n### Relevant log output\n\n_No response_\n\n### How did you obtain Bitcoin Core\n\nPre-built binaries\n\n### What version of Bitcoin Core are you using?\n\nv24.0.1\n\n### Operating system and version\n\nLinux, Tuxedo OS 2.0.2\n\n### Machine specifications\n\n20 Ã 12th Gen IntelÂ® Coreâ¢ i7-12700H\r\n62,5 GiB of RAM\r\n",
